snippet.textDisplay: ok so I just have to say #1) LOVE these two HOWEVER #2) for someone that is such an inspiration for body positivity and normalizing all things body I'm surprised by the use of "natural birth". That term has always gotten under my skin. First, the whole origination of the term came from a pretty anti-feminist position. Second, it implies that all other forms of birth are somehow "unnatural". I had three kids via c-section. There is nothing wrong with c-section. There is nothing wrong with an epidural. There is nothing wrong with being induced. I think this should more accurately be called an non-medicated home birth. Even for people who use "natural birth" it has been used on a WIDE spectrum of actual birth scenarios. For someone that stands by affirmations and realizes that words have power, realize that your words have power.
